flavorText: If it flaps its wings really fast, it can generate shock waves that will shatter windows in the area.

name: Venusaur
abilities: [{'name': 'Floral Fragrance', 'text': 'Once during your turn (before your attack), you may search your deck for a Pokémon, reveal it, and put it into your hand. Shuffle your deck afterward.', 'type': 'Ability'}]
flavorText: After a rainy day, the flower on its back smells stronger. The scent attracts other Pokémon.

name: Gengar
abilities: [{'name': 'Shadow Curse', 'text': "If Gengar would be Knocked Out by damage from an opponent's attack, you may put 3 damage counters on 1 of your opponent's Pokémon.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]

name: Heatran
flavorText: Its body is made of rugged steel. However, it is partially melted in spots because of its own heat.

name: Cradily
flavorText: It lives in the shallows of warm seas. When the tide goes out, it digs up prey from beaches.

name: Flygon
abilities: [{'name': 'Levitate', 'text': 'As long as Flygon has any Energy attached to it, the Retreat Cost for Flygon is 0.', 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]

name: Gardevoir
abilities: [{'name': 'Heal Dance', 'text': "Once during your turn (before your attack), you may remove 2 damage counter from 1 of your Pokémon. You can't use more than 1 Heal Dance Poké-Power each turn. This power can't be used if Gardevoir is affected by a Special Condition.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]

name: Darkrai
flavorText: It can lull people to sleep and make them dream. It is active during nights of the new moon.

name: Bellossom
abilities: [{'name': 'Flower Supplement', 'text': "Once during your turn (before your attack), you may flip a coin. If heads, attach 1 basic Energy card from your hand to 1 of your Benched Pokémon. This power can't be used if Bellossom is affected by a Special Condition.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]

name: Yanma
flavorText: Its eyes can see 360 degrees without moving its head. It won't miss prey—even those behind it.

name: Shuckle
flavorText: The berries stored in its vaselike shell eventually become a thick, pulpy juice.

name: Latios
flavorText: A highly intelligent Pokémon. By folding back its wings in flight, it can overtake jet planes.

name: Ampharos
flavorText: The bright light on its tail can be seen far away. It has been treasured since ancient times as a beacon.

name: Ivysaur
flavorText: When the bud on its back starts swelling, a sweet aroma wafts to indicate the flower's coming bloom.

name: Weepinbell
flavorText: The leafy parts act as cutters for slashing foes. It spits a fluid that dissolves everything.

name: Gloom
flavorText: The honey it drools from its mouth smells so atrocious, it can curl noses more than a mile away.

name: Dragonair
flavorText: If its body takes on an aura, the weather changes instantly. It is said to live in seas and lakes.

name: Dusknoir
abilities: [{'name': 'Dark Palm', 'text': "Once during your turn (before your attack), if your opponent has 4 or more Benched Pokémon, you may choose 1 of them and shuffle that Pokémon and all cards attached to it into his or her deck. This power can't be used if Dusknoir if affected by a Special Condition.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]
flavorText: The antenna on its head captures radio waves from the world of spirits that command it to take people there.

name: Entei
abilities: [{'name': 'Burning Coat', 'text': "Whenever 1 of your opponent's Pokémon is Knocked Out by damage from Entei's attacks, discard the top 3 cards from your opponent's deck.", 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]
flavorText: It is said that when it roars, a volcano erupts somewhere around the globe.

name: Hoppip
flavorText: It drifts on winds. It is said that when Hoppip gather in fields and mountains, spring is on the way.

name: Roselia
flavorText: Its flowers give off a relaxing fragrance. The stronger its aroma, the healthier the Roselia is.

name: Seedot
flavorText: When it dangles from a tree branch, it looks just like an acorn. It enjoys scaring other Pokémon.

name: Kakuna
abilities: [{'name': 'Grass Cushion', 'text': 'If this Pokémon has any Grass Energy attached to it, it takes 30 less damage from attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).', 'type': 'Ability'}]
flavorText: Almost incapable of moving, this Pokémon can only harden its shell to protect itself when it is in danger.

name: Ampharos
abilities: [{'name': 'Energy Connect', 'text': "As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), you may move a basic Energy card attached to 1 of your Benched Pokémon to your Active Pokémon. This power can't be used if Ampharos is affected by a Special Condition.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]

name: Electivire
abilities: [{'name': 'Intense Voltage', 'text': "As often as you like during your turn (before your attack), if Elekid is anywhere under Electivire, you may move a Lightning Energy attached to your Pokémon to Electivire. This power can't be used if Electivire is affected by a Special Condition.", 'type': 'Poké-Power'}]
flavorText: It pushes the tips of its two tails against the foe, then lets loose with over 20,000 volts of power.

name: Gloom
flavorText: Smells incredibly foul! However, around one out of a thousand people enjoy sniffing its nose-bending stink.

name: Hitmontop
flavorText: It launches kicks while spinning. If it spins at high speed, it may bore its way into the ground.

name: Team Aqua's Kyogre
abilities: [{'name': 'Power Saver', 'text': "As long as the number of Pokémon in play (both yours and your opponent's) that has Team Aqua in its name is 3 or less, Team Aqua's Kyogre can't attack.", 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]

name: Dragonite
flavorText: It is said to make its home somewhere in the sea. It guides crews of shipwrecks to shore.

name: Flygon
abilities: [{'name': 'Irritating Buzz', 'text': "As long as Flygon is your Active Pokémon, put 1 damage counter on each of your opponent's Active Pokémon between turns, excluding Fighting Pokémon.", 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]
flavorText: It whips up sandstorms with powerful flaps of its wings. It is known as "The Desert Spirit."

name: Servine
flavorText: They avoid attacks by sinking into the shadows of thick foliage. They retaliate with masterful whipping techniques.

name: Blissey
abilities: [{'name': 'Softboiled', 'text': 'When you play Blissey from your hand, you may flip a coin. If heads, remove 8 damage counters from Blissey. If tails, remove 4 damage counters from Blissey. Either way, if Blissey has fewer damage counters than that, remove all of them.', 'type': 'Pokémon Power'}]
flavorText: Anyone who takes even one bite of Blissey's egg becomes unfailingly caring and pleasant to everyone.

name: Dark Donphan
flavorText: The larger its tusks, the higher its status in the herd.

name: Vileplume
abilities: [{'name': 'Allergy Panic', 'text': "Apply Weakness for each Pokémon (both yours and your opponent's) as ×4 instead.", 'type': 'Ability'}]
flavorText: Its petals are the largest in the world. As it walks, it scatters extremely allergenic pollen.

name: Piplup
flavorText: Because it is very proud, it hates accepting food from people. Its thick down guards it from cold.

name: Paras
flavorText: Whether it's due to a lack of moisture or a lack of nutrients, in Alola the mushrooms on Paras don't grow up quite right.

name: Seedot
flavorText: It attaches itself to a tree branch using the top of its head. Strong winds can sometimes make it fall.

name: Blastoise δ
abilities: [{'name': 'Shield Veil', 'text': 'Each of your Active Pokémon has no Weakness.', 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]

name: Charizard
flavorText: When expelling a blast of superhot fire, the red flame at the tip of its tail burns more intensely.

name: Dialga
abilities: [{'name': 'Time Aura', 'text': "As long as Dialga is your Active Pokémon, your opponent can't play any Pokémon from his or her hand to evolve his or her Active Pokémon.", 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]
flavorText: It has the power to control time. It appears in Sinnoh-region myths as an ancient deity.

name: Pachirisu
flavorText: It makes fur balls that crackle with static electricity. It stores them with berries in tree holes.

name: Tangrowth
flavorText: Its vines grow so profusely that, in the warm season, you can't even see its eyes.

name: Nuzleaf
flavorText: The sound of its grass flute makes its listeners uneasy. It lives deep in forests.

name: Camerupt
abilities: [{'name': 'Delta Protection', 'text': "Any damage done to Camerupt by attacks from your opponent's Pokémon that has δ on its card is reduced by 40 (after applying Weakness and Resistance).", 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]

name: Dark Blastoise
flavorText: An aggressive Pokémon that tackles anything it sees.

name: Dark Espeon
flavorText: The tips of its split tail quiver whenever it uses its psychic abilities to read its opponent's next move.

name: Nidoking
abilities: [{'name': 'Pheromone Stamina', 'text': 'Nidoking gets +20 HP for each Nidoqueen you have in play.', 'type': 'Poké-Body'}]
flavorText: Its tail is thick and powerful. If it binds an enemy, it can render the victim helpless quite easily.

name: Torterra
flavorText: Some Pokémon are born on a Torterra's back and spend their entire life there.

name: Charizard
abilities: [{'name': 'Resolute Flame', 'text': "This Pokémon's attacks do 30 more damage to your opponent's Active Pokémon for each of their Pokémon-GX and Pokémon-EX in play.", 'type': 'Ability'}]
flavorText: Its wings can carry this Pokémon close to an altitude of 4,600 feet. It blows out fire at very high temperatures.

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Even in the fiercest wind, it can control its fluff to make its way to any place in the world it wants.

name: Arcanine
abilities: [{'name': 'Security Guard', 'text': "As long as this Pokémon is your Active Pokémon, all of your Pokémon take 30 less damage from your opponent's attacks (after applying Weakness and Resistance).", 'type': 'Ability'}]
flavorText: Legends tell of its fighting alongside a general and conquering a whole country.

name: Kakuna
flavorText: While awaiting evolution, it hides from predators under leaves and in nooks of branches.

name: Kricketune
flavorText: There is a village that hosts a contest based on the amazingly variable cries of this Pokémon.

name: Jumpluff
flavorText: Once it catches the wind, it deftly controls its cotton-puff spores—it can even float around the world.

name: Vileplume-GX
abilities: [{'name': 'Fragrant Flower Garden', 'text': 'Once during your turn (before your attack), you may heal 30 damage from each of your Pokémon.', 'type': 'Ability'}]

name: Treecko
flavorText: Small hooks on the bottom of its feet catch on walls and ceilings. That is how it can hang from above.

name: Clefable
flavorText: A timid Fairy Pokémon that is rarely seen. It will run and hide the moment it senses people.
